{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"9651bafa-480f-43e7-9f43-159f3c76b01b","content":"Here are the MSBuild evaluation performance issues I found:\n\n> **Note:** `${backend}` appears to be an unresolved variable — I analyzed the project directly.\n\n### 1. Recursive glob with `**\\*.*` (line 9, `.csproj`)\n```xml\n<AdditionalFiles Include=\"**\\*.*\" Exclude=\"**\\bin\\**;**\\obj\\**\" />\n```\nThis forces MSBuild to walk the **entire directory tree** on every evaluation. As the repo grows, this becomes increasingly expensive. Prefer explicit paths or narrower globs (e.g., `*.cs`).\n\n### 2. File I/O during evaluation (line 13, `.csproj`)\n```xml\n<BuildNotes …>$([System.IO.File]::ReadAllText('build-notes.txt'))</BuildNotes>\n```\nCalling `System.IO.File.ReadAllText` is a **property function that performs disk I/O during evaluation**. This blocks the evaluator and cannot be cached. Move this to a build target so it only runs when actually needed.\n\n### 3. Deeply chained `<Import>` files (3 levels)\n```\n.csproj → level1.props → level2.props → level3.props\n```\nEach import adds an additional file-open, parse, and evaluate cycle. Three levels isn't catastrophic, but the pattern compounds quickly if more layers are added. Flatten where possible.\n\n### Summary of recommended fixes\n\n| Issue | Severity | Fix |\n|---|---|---|\n| `**\\*.*` glob | **High** | Narrow to specific extensions or folders |\n| `File::ReadAllText` in property | **High** | Move to a `<Target>` with `Inputs/Outputs` |\n| 3-level import chain | **Low** | Flatten or consolidate `.props` files |\n\nThe two high-severity items — the recursive glob and the evaluation-time file read — are the main culprits for slow evaluation.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"fea3e5c5-213f-481c-9133-b43073d6c3d5","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"Now I have a full picture. Let me analyze the MSBuild evaluation performance issues.\n\nNote: The user referenced `${backend}` which looks like an unresolved template variable — I'll just note that and focus on the analysis.","outputTokens":528},"id":"c7fecbcf-4456-4a9c-8b3b-90ae4fa4c81a","timestamp":"2026-04-07T16:01:34.978Z","parentId":"35b152ab-446e-40aa-87ec-b4bc4b3ff718"}
